text: Teton County is a county in the U.S. state of Idaho. As of the 2020 census, 11,630 people lived there. The county seat is Driggs, and the largest city is Victor. The county was created in 1915 and was named after the Teton Mountains to the east. == Communities == * Bates * Driggs (county seat) * Felt * Tetonia * Victor * Cedron * Chapin * Clementsville * Cache * Darby == References == Category:1915 establishments in Idaho Category:Idaho counties
